What you need to know:  Having interacted with elite Kenyan runners for the first time in 1988, Dr Rosa made the “Kenyan breakthrough” in 1991 when he launched the “Discovery Kenya” project with the aim of selecting promising athletes and offering them the best conditions to help them succeed internationallyFrom obscurity, Dr Rosa had nurtured the careers of legends like Tergat and Tanui, nursing them through potentially career-threatening injuries to global stardomHe believes that both Brigid and men’s marathon world record holder Eliud Kipchoge (2:01:09) can improve their records